what do they want?','https://goout.net/i/129/1295066-383.jpg','2024-11-11 20:30:00','2024-11-11 22:59:59',9368,1),(21786,'Love Lies Bleeding','Reclusive gym manager Lou falls hard for Jackie, an ambitious bodybuilder headed through town to Vegas in pursuit of her dream. But their love ignites violence, pulling them deep into the web of Lou\'s criminal family.','https://goout.net/i/131/1315098-383.jpg','2024-11-12 15:45:00','2024-11-12 22:59:59',9368,2),(21787,'Bad Luck Banging or Loony Porn','Emi, a school teacher, finds her career and reputation under threat after a personal sex tape is leaked on the Internet. Forced to meet the parents demanding her dismissal, Emi refuses to surrender to their pressure.','https://goout.net/i/100/1001886-383.jpg','2024-11-12 16:00:00','2024-11-12 22:59:59',9368,1),(21788,'Smoke Sauna Sisterhood','Award-winning film at the Sundance Film Festival about a group of women gathering in a traditional sauna to share their deepest secrets, thoughts and draw strength from togetherness. Surrounded by smoke, they bare not only their bodies, but also their emotions. The viewer learns what they experienced in their lives. *Smoke Sauna Sisterhood* is filled with authentic beauty that comes not from having a perfect body, but from humor, wisdom and self-awareness.','https://goout.net/i/122/1226263-383.jpg','2024-11-12 17:45:00','2024-11-12 22:59:59',9368,1),(21789,'Yamato','# Spectacular group Yamato – the world\'s most famous Japanese drummers – return to Poland with their latest show *The Wings of the Phoenix* as part of a new world tour.\n\nOne-of-a-kind original sounds of the Far East, a huge dose of optimism, spiritual energy and thrills. The sounds produced by the musicians are inspired by traditional Japanese music, but are its contemporary, subversive variations. Each artist leads their own cabaret-theatre show. Breathtaking solo performances are interspersed with phenomenal, trance-like group pieces. The Yamato ensemble is renowned for its visually spectacular shows featuring the art of playing traditional taiko drums.','https://goout.net/i/097/974291-383.jpg','2024-11-12 18:00:00','2024-11-12 22:59:59',9538,1),(21790,'Close','The intense friendship between two thirteen-year old boys Léo and Rémi suddenly gets disrupted. Struggling to understand what has happened, Léo approaches Sophie, Rémi\'s mother. *Close* is a film about friendship and responsibility.','https://goout.net/i/111/1118931-383.jpg','2024-11-12 19:30:00','2024-11-12 22:59:59',9368,2),(21791,'Coffee and Cigarettes','11 vignettes over coffee and cigarettes. In these often improvised segments, Jarmusch allows the characters, but also the actors, to meet for a moment. Tom Waits and Iggy Pop, Steve Coogan and Alfred Molina, Bill Murray with RZA and GZA, Cate Blanchett with... Cate Blanchett and many more stop for a moment at the café tables to talk about alternative medicine, their common ancestors, Elvis Presley or the 1920s in Paris.','https://goout.net/i/050/506399-383.jpg','2024-11-13 16:00:00','2024-11-13 22:59:59',9368,1),(21792,'The Farewell','A Chinese family discovers their grandmother has only a short while left to live and decide to keep her in the dark, scheduling a wedding to gather before she dies.','https://goout.net/i/093/931304-383.jpg','2024-11-13 16:15:00','2024-11-13 22:59:59',9368,2),(21793,'Queerowy klub filmowy: The Neon Demon','Following two films with Ryan Gosling, Nicolas Winding Refn enlists Elle Fanning for the dazzling, hypnotic *Neon Demon* – an entrancing and especially stylized indictment of the ugliest grotesqueries of the modelling industry. Fanning plays Jesse, an aspiring model who moves to Los Angeles, where her youth and vitality are devoured by a group of beauty-obsessed women who will take any means necessary to get what she has.','https://goout.net/i/077/776727-383.jpg','2024-11-13 18:00:00','2024-11-13 22:59:59',9368,1),(21794,'Nosowska & Król','# Nosowska and Król are reuniting as a unique duo. This autumn, they are announcing a joint album *Kasia i Błażej* and a tour *Jenin-Piaseczno* promoting the release.\n\nThe *Jenin-Piaseczno* tour will play in several of Poland\'s largest cities and will take place in seated music halls and theatres. All this is so that the listeners can focus on the textual and musical layer of the new album *Kasia i Błażej* in comfortable conditions. Katarzyna Nosowska is a singer, lyricist, writer and one of the most expressive personalities and artists in the country. Błażej Król is a musician, composer, singer and songwriter. They have already collaborated together in 2023, where they performed, among others, a cover of Nirvana\'s *Smells Like Teen Spirit* or Young Leosia\'s *Glasses* during their summer tour. Then, in autumn 2023, they released the track *Neodym*.','https://goout.net/i/063/634374-383.jpg','2024-11-13 19:00:00','2024-11-13 22:59:59',9474,1),(21795,'Black Coal, Thin Ice','An ex cop and his ex partner decide to follow up on investigation of a series of murders that ended their careers and shamed them, when identical murders begin again.','https://goout.net/i/131/1316619-383.jpg','2024-11-13 20:00:00','2024-11-13 22:59:59',9368,1),(21796,'Handling the Undead','On a hot summer day in Oslo, the dead mysteriously awaken, and three families are thrown into chaos when their deceased loved ones come back to them. Who are they, and what do they want?','https://goout.net/i/129/1295066-383.jpg','2024-11-13 20:15:00','2024-11-13 22:59:59',9368,1),(21797,'Love Lies Bleeding','Reclusive gym manager Lou falls hard for Jackie, an ambitious bodybuilder headed through town to Vegas in pursuit of her dream. But their love ignites violence, pulling them deep into the web of Lou\'s criminal family.','https://goout.net/i/131/1315098-383.jpg','2024-11-14 16:00:00','2024-11-14 22:59:59',9368,2),(21798,'Co robimy w ukryciu','Only the New Zealand Documentary Board would take a stake in an up-close and personal “under the cape” look at four vampires and a guy named Stu bringing several thousand years of collective baggage into a shared living space. The dynamics of being undead while dealing with a duty wheel (disposing of their unique “leftovers” is a chore) and the constant threat of fatal sunburn keeps Vlad and the other lads at each other\'s throats. *Flight of the Conchords* Jemaine Clement and Taika Waititi (*Eagle vs Shark*) have created a timeless, or even eternal, comedy. Follow the lives of Viago, Deacon, and Vladislav, three flatmates who are just trying to get by and overcome life\'s obstacles - like being immortal vampires who must feast on human blood. Hundreds of years old, the vampires are finding that beyond sunlight catastrophes, hitting the main artery, and not being able to get a sense of their wardrobe without a reflection, modern society has them struggling with the mundane like paying rent, trying to get into nightclubs, and overcoming flatmate conflicts.','https://goout.net/i/089/891504-383.jpg','2024-11-14 16:15:00','2024-11-14 22:59:59',9368,1),(21799,'Krypta Show: Good Boy','# Krypta Show at Kino Amondo is a film night featuring obscure cinema full of absurd and ridiculous places, people and situations every Thursday at 20:00.\n\nAudiences can look forward to unreal stories with unexpected twists and surreal scenes that will stir their imagination. The series is overseen by Paweł Trzepizur of the project Krypta Absurdu, dedicated to B-movies. During a short lecture before each screening, he will outline the necessary context around the title watched, while after the screening he will ask the audience for their opinion and lead a conversation (not only) about the film they have watched – in this case, Viljar Bøe\'s *Good Boy*.\n\nOn the surface, Christian (Gard Løkke) is the perfect candidate for a boyfriend, if not immediately for a husband – he is young and handsome, cares about physical fitness, and has inherited fat millions from his parents. What\'s more, he loves dogs and takes care of his pet, Frank. Any red flags? Well, one. Frank is no ordinary dog. He\'s a grown man dressed up in a dog costume, whom Christian treats like a pet.','https://goout.net/i/121/1214686-383.jpg','2024-11-14 18:00:00','2024-11-14 22:59:59',9368,1),(21800,'Krypta Show','# Krypta Show at Kino Amondo is a film night featuring obscure cinema full of absurd and ridiculous places, people and situations every Thursday at 20:00.\n\nAudiences can look forward to unreal stories with unexpected twists and surreal scenes that will stir their imagination. The series is overseen by Paweł Trzepizur of the project Krypta Absurdu, dedicated to B-movies. During a short lecture before each screening, he will outline the necessary context around the title watched, while after the screening he will ask the audience for their opinion and lead a conversation (not only) about the film they have watched. The titles of the films to be screened remain a secret.','https://goout.net/i/117/1173627-383.jpg','2024-11-14 18:00:00','2024-11-14 22:59:59',9368,1),(21801,'Drive My Car','Drive My Car, based on a short story from the collection *Men Without Women*, is an intimate story about the complex love relationship between a prominent actor and director and a woman who keeps many secrets from him. Hamaguchi bases his film on precise dialogues and brilliantly drawn characters. It is a story about unconditional acceptance of a loved one and of oneself and one\'s imperfections, at the same time a beautiful and moving ode to life.','https://goout.net/i/106/1067855-383.jpg','2024-11-14 19:30:00','2024-11-14 22:59:59',9368,2),(21802,'The Wailing','A stranger arrives in a little village and soon after a mysterious sickness starts spreading. A policeman is drawn into the incident and is forced to solve the mystery in order to save his daughter.','https://goout.net/i/042/422750-383.jpg','2024-11-14 19:45:00','2024-11-14 22:59:59',9368,2),(21803,'Illusion + Frontside + Hostia','# Illusion is embarking on a nationwide tour. This unique event will allow fans to relive the magic of their music and also see the bands Frontside and Hostia.\n\nIllusion are undoubtedly one of the most important rock bands in Poland. Their history dates back to 1992, when, in Gdańsk, former She and Skawalker musician Tomasz ‘Lipa’ Lipnicki, Jerzy ‘Jerry’ Rutkowski and Paweł Herbasch founded the band. The first Illusion concert took place in February 1992 in Gdańsk, and already in August of the same year, Jarosław Śmigiel joined them. In this line-up, the band functions to this day. Illusion\'s debut album was released in 1993, which featured vocalist Grzegorz ‘Guzik’ Guziński and guitarist Janusz Sokołowski as guests. Illusion concerts are invariably hugely popular. The band is known for their energetic performances, which infect the audience with an incredible dose of rock energy. During the upcoming tour, fans will have the opportunity to hear them in cities such as Warsaw, Krakow and Poznań.\n\nThe upcoming tour will also be special for fans of the band Frontside, who will be reminding fans of their third album *The Twilight of the Gods - First Step to a Mental Revolution*. This album premiered in October 2004 and this year celebrates its 20th anniversary. To celebrate, Mystic Production will reissue this classic release on CD and for the first time as an LP. One of Frontside\'s most recognisable songs - *Our Destiny is to Burn* - comes from this album. During the tour, Frontside will present a set based on this iconic album, but without forgetting other key songs from throughout their career. The band, known for their dynamic live shows, has this time prepared a completely new setlist that is sure to delight both regular fans and new listeners.\n\nHostia is a Polish revelation of recent years on the grindcore scene. Known for their brutal, uncompromising songs, the band quickly won the hearts of heavy sound lovers. Their music combines fast, aggressive sounds with a rocking groove and catchy patents hidden under a layer of noise. Hostia have released one EP and three full-length albums, the latest of which *Nailed* was released in November 2022 on Deformeathing Productions.','https://goout.net/i/099/999227-383.jpg','2024-11-15 18:00:00','2024-11-15 22:59:59',9539,1),(21804,'Visual Concert','The more than 80-strong CoOperate Symphony Orchestra accompanied by the Choir (under the direction of Mariusz Otto, Chorusmaster of the Grand Theatre in Poznan) under the baton of Adam Domurat will fill the musical space to the rhythm of a film image showing the most spectacular places, amazing animals, interesting people and unique moments captured by the eye of the camera. From paradisiacal beaches, the 7 Wonders of the World, extraordinary National Parks, rainforests, ocean depths, snow-capped mountain peaks to urban jungles around the world. The concert will be graced by soloists: Kasia Moś, Beata Bielska, Krzysztof Iwaneczko. In a symphonic sound, you will hear works from such films as *Star Wars*, *Pirates of the Caribbean*, *Iron Man*, *The Dark Knight*, *Braveheart*, *Lord of the Rings*, *Skyfall*, *Romeo and Juliet*, *The Greatest Showman*, *Spirit*, *X-Men*, *The Lion King* or works of epic music by the world-famous Two Steps from Hell.','https://goout.net/i/127/1279099-383.jpg','2024-11-15 18:00:00','2024-11-15 22:59:59',9540,1),(21805,'Miły ATZ','# Miły ATZ will visit the biggest Polish cities with his *Acid Moro Tour*.\n\nMiły ATZ has been working on his latest album, closing his publishing trilogy, for two years, and it is by far the artist\'s biggest project to date. On the two full-length records, the rapper prepared as many as 28 tracks filled with unobvious experiments, but also with what fans appreciate most - ATZ\'s typical fusion of styles and trends, in which he moves with ease. And so will be the concerts of the *Acid Moro Tour*. The musical universe will, of course, be enriched with the greatest classics from the rapper\'s concert repertoire.','https://goout.net/i/130/1303606-383.jpg','2024-11-15 19:00:00','2024-11-15 22:59:59',9541,1),(21806,'Lej Mi Pół','# Comedy rock group Lej Mi Pół is embarking on a fall tour of Poland.\n\nLej Mi Pół is a group that is closer to stand-up than to a classical music group. Here, the music, while undeniably catchy, is the backdrop for everything that happens in between... and you never know what\'s going to happen there. Lej Mi Pół has been attracting crowds of absurd humour enthusiasts to concerts for nearly a decade. Their cutting language, distance from themselves and the unmistakable chemistry between the band members act as a self-perpetuating machine of madness. There is no question of any distance between the musicians and the audience. The trio\'s performances are unmissable.','https://goout.net/i/121/1215344-383.jpg','2024-11-15 19:00:00','2024-11-15 22:59:59',9503,1),(21807,'Young Igi','# Young Igi is embarking on his last solo concerts to promote his album *Ekskluzywny głód*, where he will visit the biggest Polish cities.\n\nEach concert is a specially prepared show, completely different from the performances that listeners may be familiar with from the festival tour. Special surprises and special guests will be waiting for Igi\'s fans.','https://goout.net/i/129/1298990-383.jpg','2024-11-15 19:00:00','2024-11-15 22:59:59',9349,1),(21808,'Edyta Bartosiewicz','# Edyta Bartosiewicz is embarking on a jubilee concert tour. The artist will perform in Polish concert halls and philharmonics, where, accompanied by a symphony orchestra, she will play songs from her album *Sen*, released thirty years ago.\n\n*Sen* is Edyta Bartosiewicz\'s second solo album after *Love*. Released in September 1994, the album turned out to be a breakthrough in the artist\'s career - her first attempt at writing in her native language was extremely successful. Songs such as *Koziorożec*, *Tatuaż*, *Urodziny* or the title track *Sen* permanently entered the canon of Polish pop culture. The album was a huge success, selling several hundred thousand copies and going platinum many times over. It was awarded the Fryderyk for \"Best Rock Album\" during the first edition of these awards in 1995.  Edyta Bartosiewicz was also awarded the title of \"Best Female Vocalist\" at that time.','https://goout.net/i/126/1261844-383.jpg','2024-11-15 19:00:00','2024-11-15 22:59:59',9527,1),(21809,'De Łindows + Lock Down','# Bands De Łindows and Lock Down in Trzciel.\n\nThe rock band De Łindows was formed in Katowice, Poland, in 2002, and has had concerts in Poland, the Czech Republic and Slovakia. They have performed at, among others, Przystanek Woodstock/Pol\'and\'Rock Festival (three times), B-Festival, Jarocin, Punk Island (SK), Underground Fest (SK), Keltska Noc (CZ), Hajnówka Rock Festival, Punk Fest and Chad Festival. They have supported Kult and Pull the Wire, among others. They have seven albums to their credit, the latest of which is *Pożar w burdelu*, released in 2022.\n\nPoznan-based band Lock Down is probably the youngest hardcore punk band in Poland, ranging from 10 to 14 years of age. The mastermind behind the project is Krzysztof Skurski, father of one of the members and the former drummer of legendary Polish hardcore group Apatia. Lock Down debuted with the album *We Are the Change* in 2023.','https://goout.net/i/103/1038785-383.jpg','2024-11-16 18:00:00','2024-11-16 22:59:59',9542,1),(21810,'Illusion + Frontside + Hostia','# Illusion is embarking on a nationwide tour. This unique event will allow fans to relive the magic of their music and also see the bands Frontside and Hostia.\n\nIllusion are undoubtedly one of the most important rock bands in Poland. Their history dates back to 1992, when, in Gdańsk, former She and Skawalker musician Tomasz ‘Lipa’ Lipnicki, Jerzy ‘Jerry’ Rutkowski and Paweł Herbasch founded the band. The first Illusion concert took place in February 1992 in Gdańsk, and already in August of the same year, Jarosław Śmi